body:
I'm testing a patch of mine, if it deadlocks, that means the bug is
fixed/better-hidden?
(Sorry if the deadlock is obviously intended, I'm learning my Go on a
street corner.)


On Mon, Apr 13, 2015 at 11:09 PM, Brad Fitzpatrick <notifications@github.com
> wrote:

> I whittled it down to this:
>
> package main
>
> func main() {
>         dst := &T{
>                 fn: func(error) error { return nil },
>         }
>         dst.Get()
> }
>
> type T struct {
>         c   <-chan error
>         fn  func(error) error
>         err error
> }
>
> func (t *T) Set(err error) {
>         if t.fn != nil && err != nil {
>                 err = t.fn(err)
>         }
> }
>
> func (t *T) Get() error {
>         t.Set(<-t.c)
>         return t.err
> }
>
> If you go run that, it'll crash the same way.
>
